  <summary date="2006-04-05T21:55:32Z" status="Introduced in House">Citizen Soldier Protection Act of 2006 - Prohibits any member of the Armed Forces from being required to: (1) wear as part of the uniform any badge, symbol, headgear, or other visible indicia or insignia of the United Nations (U.N.) or any foreign state; or (2) serve in any capacity under any officer of the U.N. or a foreign state except as specifically provided by law, and then only during a time of war declared by Congress.</summary>
